        management portfolios. Volume geographies: San Fernando Valley rental-heavy areas (Panorama City,
        North Hills, Van Nuys, Reseda, Arleta), East LA and Boyle Heights multifamily, South Bay rentals
        (Long Beach, Compton, Lynwood, Carson), inland-Valley apartment buildings (Pomona, West Covina,
        Baldwin Park, Ontario, Fontana, Rancho Cucamonga). Property-management standing accounts typically
        run 20–100 Amana / Whirlpool-family fridges across multi-building portfolios, and our preventive-
        maintenance scheduling keeps these units running well past the typical first-major-repair
        threshold.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Amana refrigerator failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Warm fridge compartment — condenser coil dust (top failure)</h3>
        <p>
          Most common Amana service call, especially in summer. Budget-durability fridges run compressors
          longer and harder than premium units, and coil dust buildup reduces heat rejection quickly in
          LA's hot kitchen environments. Rental-property kitchens with limited ventilation accelerate
          this. Condenser clean + diagnostic $140–$220. Best preventive service on a rental portfolio —
          scheduled annually catches most cooling issues before they become tenant complaints.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Door gasket compression loss in rental-turnover scenarios</h3>
        <p>
          Budget-platform gaskets lose seal quality faster than premium gaskets — typically at 6–8 years
          of normal use, faster in rental-turnover where doors get slammed. Gasket replacement $200–$340.
          Common 6-plus-year service on rental-installed base.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Cold-control drift on mechanical-dial units</h3>
        <p>
          Older Amana with mechanical cold-control dials drift over time — the setpoint produces a warmer
          compartment than the dial reads. Classic fix is cold-control swap $180–$280. Newer Amana with
          electronic controls has different failure pattern (board fault vs dial drift).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Defrost timer / heater on 10-plus-year units</h3>
        <p>
          Amana's simple defrost-timer + heater architecture is reliable long-term but eventually fails
          at 10–15 year age. Timer swap $180–$260; heater + thermostat $220–$340. Common on rental-
          property installed base given the age distribution.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Compressor start relay + run capacitor</h3>
        <p>
          Capacitor aging at 8–12 years produces intermittent starting or complete start failure. Swap
          $180–$280. Common service on long-installed rental units.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Ice-maker module failures (trim-optional units)</h3>
        <p>
          When Amana fridges ship with factory ice makers, modules fail at 6–10 years. Module $260–$400.
          On rental-property accounts where ice-maker use is inconsistent, sometimes the decision is to
          disable the ice maker rather than repair — judgment call per account.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

